         <abstract>
            <p>The "full cost" method of accounting for the costs of finding oil represents an important departure from conventional practice in the petroleum industry. Differences in the treatment of intangible drilling and development costs will cause financial statements prepared under the full cost method to differ significantly from statements prepared conventionally.</p>
          </abstract>
